article.description: Freshman Sydney Raggio scored 15 points, including a 15-foot jumper with 2.7 seconds left, and Saint Mary's shocked No. 18 California 64-63 on Saturday in the Cal Classic.
article.headline: Raggio, Saint Mary's upsets No. 18 Cal women 64-63
article.linkText: Raggio, Saint Mary's knock off No. 18 Cal 64-63
article.story:
BERKELEY, Calif. -- Freshman Sydney Raggio scored 15 points, including a 15-foot jumper with 2.7 seconds left, and Saint Mary's shocked No. 18 California 64-63 on Saturday in the Cal Classic.

Asha Thomas missed a 3-pointer at the buzzer for Cal.

Kristine Anigwe, who had a career-high 27 points and 12 rebounds, put back her own miss with 29.1 seconds to play to put the Golden Bears in front.

Devon Brookshire and Megan McKay added 12 points apiece for the Gaels (6-2).

Mikayla Cowling had 12 points for Cal (5-2), which had a 10-point lead in the first quarter but led just 33-32 at the half as Raggio scored 10 points. The Bears shot 31 percent in the second half.

It is the just the fourth time in 37 Cal Classics, and the first time since the tournament went to four teams in 1983, the Golden Bears did not make the championship game.
